HTML routes come from directory position, not from the `#` filename.

### Directory routes

[codeblock, $code("text"):
    src/#page.bst  -> index.html
    src/about/#page.bst  -> about/index.html
]

The root module is the home page. Each nested directory gets its own route.

### API-only modules

A module with only exports and no page activity produces no HTML. Not every `#*.bst` file becomes a page.

### Remember

- Routes come from directories.
- The `#` filename does not choose the route.
- API-only modules produce no HTML artifact.